The provided C code demonstrates one way to solve this. The core logic is to initialize a variable `largest` with the first element of the array. Then, loop through the remaining elements, and if an element is found to be greater than `largest`, update `largest` with that element's value. A correct implementation in C would be:
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int arr[] = {10, 45, 3, 99, 23};
    int n = sizeof(arr) / sizeof(arr[0]);
    int largest = arr[0];
    for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
        if (arr[i] > largest) {
            largest = arr[i];
        }
    }
    printf("Largest number: %d", largest);
    return 0;
}
